00:29:59.909 --> 00:30:01.310
For the Israelites, it is the same dirt.

00:30:04.514 --> 00:30:08.018
Different day.

00:30:08.038 --> 00:30:09.860
Until this guy named Jesus pops up, right?

00:30:10.441 --> 00:30:11.602
And he's doing it different.

00:30:12.514 --> 00:30:13.295
He's healing people.

00:30:15.379 --> 00:30:17.803
He's talking about the kingdom of God and all this stuff.

00:30:19.145 --> 00:30:19.907
And the word gets out.

00:30:20.127 --> 00:30:21.429
People are like, hey, have you heard about Jesus?

00:30:22.130 --> 00:30:23.353
Oh my gosh, yeah, I heard about Jesus.

00:30:23.373 --> 00:30:24.214
I already healed somebody.

00:30:24.354 --> 00:30:25.336
Well, I already said this.

00:30:25.977 --> 00:30:29.483
Whoa, that kind of sounds like, is this the guy?

00:30:29.683 --> 00:30:30.966
Guys, this might be the guy.

00:30:31.126 --> 00:30:32.348
Guys, this is definitely the guy.

00:30:32.869 --> 00:30:34.452
Guys, he's the guy.

00:30:34.792 --> 00:30:38.258
They're starting to freak out a little bit because they're like, this is it.

00:30:38.402 --> 00:30:39.163
Here he comes.

00:30:39.483 --> 00:30:43.728
Just like Moses freed us from Egypt, Jesus is going to free us from Rome.

00:30:46.370 --> 00:30:49.093
But we know that's not what Jesus came to do.

00:30:50.695 --> 00:30:56.541
We can see in the rear view mirror that what they didn't realize was that Jesus wasn't the Messiah that they wanted.

00:30:57.422 --> 00:30:59.063
He was the Messiah they needed, guys.

00:31:00.325 --> 00:31:05.490
He came to free them not from Rome, not from human oppression, but from their own sin.

00:31:05.954 --> 00:31:08.938
from the hole in their heart that they couldn't do anything to fill.

00:31:10.179 --> 00:31:15.365
The same people who were celebrating Him on Sunday were crucifying Him on Friday because they thought that He was the wrong guy.

00:31:18.889 --> 00:31:24.356
But looking back, we can see the beauty of the palm branches.

00:31:25.857 --> 00:31:26.618
Because what do they do?

00:31:26.658 --> 00:31:27.820
They cut these palm branches down.

00:31:27.840 --> 00:31:29.522
They put them in the dirt.

00:31:29.682 --> 00:31:33.106
They lie them in the street as a symbol.

00:31:33.954 --> 00:31:34.635
of surrender.

00:31:34.675 --> 00:31:38.279
This is what they would do when an invading nation would come and take over a city.

00:31:38.300 --> 00:31:39.741
They would lay palm branches in the ground.

00:31:39.761 --> 00:31:40.703
Is it to say you win?

00:31:41.123 --> 00:31:41.904
We surrender.

00:31:42.745 --> 00:31:44.928
They thought that Rome was surrendering to Jesus.

00:31:45.489 --> 00:31:46.129
News flash.

00:31:46.530 --> 00:31:47.932
It was so much bigger than that.

00:31:48.633 --> 00:31:53.359
It was a picture of you and me and all of humanity surrendering to Jesus.

00:31:54.020 --> 00:31:57.844
It was a picture of what he does in your heart when you say yes to him.

00:31:58.645 --> 00:32:02.290
He walks in and where Jesus walks

00:32:02.786 --> 00:32:07.251
It changes ordinary dirt into something beautiful, into a miracle.

00:32:08.412 --> 00:32:11.015
Same dirt, different day.

00:32:13.878 --> 00:32:14.599
But it keeps going.

00:32:16.521 --> 00:32:17.342
I wasn't planning on crying.

00:32:19.605 --> 00:32:20.386
It's five days later.

00:32:20.406 --> 00:32:20.926
What do they do?

00:32:20.966 --> 00:32:21.387
They kill them.

00:32:23.289 --> 00:32:23.730
They kill them.

00:32:24.771 --> 00:32:26.112
And I'll save you the details.

00:32:26.152 --> 00:32:26.813
It's pretty intense.

00:32:28.475 --> 00:32:29.636
Pretty hectic, honestly.

00:32:30.317 --> 00:32:31.218
They kill them real good.

00:32:33.154 --> 00:32:36.999
But in my mind, they make one slight miscalculation.

00:32:38.781 --> 00:32:41.325
Because they kill them like they would kill any other man.

00:32:41.365 --> 00:32:44.609
And then what do they do?

00:32:46.231 --> 00:32:46.792
They get a tomb.

00:32:48.555 --> 00:32:50.457
They put him in the ground.

00:32:51.959 --> 00:32:54.042
Just like you would with a normal guy, right?

00:32:56.906 --> 00:33:00.210
One could say they bury him in the dirt.

00:33:02.562 --> 00:33:04.605
We've spent a little bit of time here together, you guys.

00:33:05.546 --> 00:33:07.709
I think we all know what God can do with a little bit of dirt.

00:33:09.632 --> 00:33:14.118
The same dirt they put him under on Friday is coming up out of on Sunday.

00:33:14.959 --> 00:33:16.661
Same dirt, different day.

00:33:18.504 --> 00:33:25.233
And now today in this moment, if you say yes to Jesus, just like him, when they killed him, he didn't die.

00:33:27.016 --> 00:33:28.377
You don't have to suffer that fate either.

00:33:29.659 --> 00:33:31.762
You, when you breathe your last,

00:33:32.226 --> 00:33:33.908
It can be standing on eternity's shore.

00:33:34.769 --> 00:33:46.925
And the meaning of this message can mean so much more to you as the dirt and the soil and the difficulty and the purposelessness and the rudderlessness of a life without God is washed away.

00:33:48.767 --> 00:33:50.910
And it's truly a different day for you.

00:33:51.911 --> 00:33:53.233
I'm gonna give you a chance to do that right now.

00:33:53.253 --> 00:33:53.774
Let's pray together.

00:33:53.814 --> 00:33:54.775
God, we love you so much.

00:33:55.936 --> 00:34:00.402
And we are humbled and honored that we get to be here in this moment.

00:34:03.586 --> 00:34:07.051
And God, there's people who are listening to this message where they just feel you speaking to them.

00:34:07.912 --> 00:34:11.556
They feel you tugging on the corner of their heart, knocking.

00:34:11.576 --> 00:34:16.403
It says in scripture that you stand at the door and knock and whoever opens the door, you will come in.

00:34:20.728 --> 00:34:31.122
Right now in this moment, Jesus, we know you want to turn an ordinary soul into something beautiful and vibrant and new.

00:34:34.786 --> 00:34:38.170
So have your way in this moment.

00:34:38.190 --> 00:34:40.913
And wherever you're watching right now, maybe you're driving.

00:34:42.374 --> 00:34:43.556
Hopefully you're not watching and driving.

00:34:45.998 --> 00:34:49.943
Sitting on the couch, maybe a friend had you over for breakfast and church.

00:34:51.665 --> 00:35:00.535
If you feel that tug, if you feel God speaking to you right now, say yes to him.

00:35:02.677 --> 00:35:03.698
Say yes to Jesus.

00:35:03.778 --> 00:35:05.941
Let him come into your life and change you forever.

00:35:06.823 --> 00:35:07.644
You will not regret it.

00:35:08.405 --> 00:35:10.709
It'll be the best decision you could ever make.

00:35:11.931 --> 00:35:14.054
Now I want to lead you in a prayer.

00:35:14.815 --> 00:35:19.342
And I believe there's not really anything special about these words that I'm saying, that you're saying.

00:35:20.303 --> 00:35:25.912
It's more just an outward statement about what I believe is happening on the inside.

00:35:26.673 --> 00:35:27.515
Say these words after me.

00:35:27.615 --> 00:35:30.259
Say, Jesus, I know I'm a sinner.

00:35:31.521 --> 00:35:32.402
I need your grace.

00:35:33.538 --> 00:35:34.380
come into my life.

00:35:35.985 --> 00:35:38.773
Make me new from this day forward.

00:35:40.358 --> 00:35:40.879
I'm all yours.

00:35:42.263 --> 00:35:42.604
Amen.

00:35:42.624 --> 00:35:47.538
Come on, we are celebrating with every single one of you who's making that decision today.
